HEADWORD: Actinaria
<hw>Ac`ti*na"ri*a</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
from Gr. <?/, <?/, ray.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>An order of
Anthozoa, including those which have simple tentacles and do not form
stony corals. Sometimes, in a wider sense, applied to all the Anthozoa,
expert the Alcyonaria, whether forming corals or not.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

